  <div id="title">CRIS KESZ VALDEZ</div>
  <div id="dates">Gift of Hope</div>
  <div id="img-div"><img id="image" src="https://peace-post.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Selman_PeacePost_Philippines_Cris_Kesz_Valdez_01.jpg"> <div id="img-caption">Kesz as he raises the trophy as an awardee of the International Children's Peace Prize, held in The Hague, Netherlands, in 2012. He found the Championing Community Children, which aspires to bring hope to desolate children across his community.</div></div>
  <div id="tribute-info">Kez was born in 1998. Throughout his childhood he was tragically abused by both of his parents. At a young age of seven he vowed to help street children, with his first steps being donating all his birthday presents to the various street children in his town in Cavite, Philippines. <br></div>
  <div id="tribute-info2">Escaping from his family, he was forced to live as a street child himself, begging in the day and sleeping on graves in the night. He was then adopted by Manalaysay who inspired him to do charity work at the said young age. He won the International Children's Peace Prize, and used the prize money to fund his charity programs. He aspires to be a medical doctor to help even more. So far he has helped over ten thousand children through his charity.</div>
  <div id="link">Learn more about him with <a id="tribute-link" href="https://www.thextraordinary.org/cris-kesz-valdez" target="_blank">this link</a>.
